.TH JOB_SCRAPER 1 "2026-03-15" "1.0" "Cybersecurity Job Tools"
.SH NAME
job_scraper \- scrape and filter cybersecurity/IT job listings from LinkedIn
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B python3 job_scraper.py [\-\-location \fILOCATION\fR] [\-\-max-per-term \fIN\fR]
.B                        [\-\-delay \fISECONDS\fR] [\-\-no-verify]
.B                        [\-\-output \fIPATH\fR] [\-\-json \fIPATH\fR]
.fi
.PP
Or as a Python module:
.PP
.nf
.B from job_scraper import JobScraper, verify_jobs, save_to_csv

scraper = JobScraper(location=\fILOCATION\fR, delay=\fISECONDS\fR)
jobs    = scraper.search(terms=\fILIST\fR, max_per_term=\fIN\fR)
jobs    = verify_jobs(jobs, scraper.session)
save_to_csv(jobs, path=\fIPATH\fR)
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBjob_scraper\fR scrapes cybersecurity and IT job listings from LinkedIn
and applies heuristic analysis to filter out fake, scam, or low-quality
postings.
.PP
An optional second-pass verification step checks each listing for
active/closed status and searches DuckDuckGo for a matching company careers
page, producing a priority-ranked output suitable for a focused job search.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI "\-\-location " LOCATION
City and state to filter listings by.
Default: \fB"Salt Lake City, UT"\fR.
.TP
.BI "\-\-max-per-term " N
Maximum number of results to collect per search term. Default: \fB25\fR.
.TP
.BI "\-\-delay " SECONDS
Seconds to sleep between requests. Increase to reduce rate-limiting risk.
Default: \fB2.0\fR.
.TP
.B \-\-no-verify
Skip the verification pass. Faster, but jobs will not be status-ranked.
.TP
.BI "\-\-output " PATH
CSV output path. Default: \fBjobs.csv\fR.
.TP
.BI "\-\-json " PATH
Also save results as JSON to this path. Optional.
.SH DATA MODEL
All results are returned as \fBJob\fR dataclass instances with the following fields:
.TP
.B title
Job title as shown in the listing.
.TP
.B company
Hiring company name.
.TP
.B location
Job location extracted from the listing.
.TP
.B snippet
Benefit text from the search card. Often empty for LinkedIn results, which
do not expose full descriptions in static HTML.
.TP
.B url
Direct link to the job listing.
.TP
.B salary
Salary range if shown in the search card; \fBNone\fR otherwise.
.TP
.B posted
Posting date string or ISO date if available; \fBNone\fR otherwise.
.TP
.B is_fake
\fBTrue\fR if the fake-job detector flagged this listing.
.TP
.B fake_reasons
List of strings describing each flag that was raised.
.TP
.B status
Verification status assigned by \fBverify_jobs()\fR. One of \fBGolden\fR,
\fBActive\fR, \fBUnknown\fR, or \fBLikely Closed\fR. Defaults to \fBUnknown\fR
before verification is run.
.TP
.B company_url
URL of the job on the company's own careers site, if found during
verification; \fBNone\fR otherwise.
.SH CLASSES
.SS JobScraper
.TP
.BI "JobScraper(location=" "\"Salt Lake City, UT\"" ", delay=" "2.0" ", session=" "None" ")"
Initialise the scraper.
.RS
.TP
.B location
City and state to filter listings by.
.TP
.B delay
Seconds to sleep between paginated requests.
.TP
.B session
Optional \fBrequests.Session\fR to reuse. A new session is created if not provided.
.RE
.TP
.BI "search(terms=" "None" ", max_per_term=" "25" ")"
Run searches for each term and return deduplicated jobs that passed the
fake-job filter. Returns a \fBlist[Job]\fR.
.TP
.BI "search_raw(terms=" "None" ", max_per_term=" "25" ")"
Identical to \fBsearch()\fR but returns all collected jobs including those
flagged as fake. Useful for auditing the filter's decisions.
.SH FUNCTIONS
.TP
.BI "detect_fake(job)"
Analyse a single \fBJob\fR and return a \fB(is_fake, reasons)\fR tuple.
.TP
.BI "verify_jobs(jobs, session, delay=" "2.0" ")"
Second-pass verification. For each job:
.RS
.IP 1. 3
Fetches the LinkedIn listing URL to check for 404 or closed-job language.
.IP 2. 3
If active, queries DuckDuckGo for the job title and company on non-aggregator
sites. A hit sets \fBstatus = "Golden"\fR and populates \fBcompany_url\fR.
.PP
Mutates \fBjob.status\fR and \fBjob.company_url\fR in place and returns the
same list.
.RE
.TP
.BI "save_to_csv(jobs, path=" "\"jobs.csv\"" ")"
Write jobs to a CSV file. Rows sorted \fBGolden \(-> Active \(-> Unknown \(->
Likely Closed\fR. The \fBfake_reasons\fR list is joined with \fB" | "\fR.
.SH DEFAULT SEARCH TERMS
When no \fIterms\fR argument is supplied, the following queries are used:
.PP
.RS
cybersecurity, information security analyst, penetration tester, SOC analyst,
network security engineer, IT support, systems administrator, cloud security
engineer, DevSecOps
.RE
.SH VERIFICATION STATUSES
.TP
.B Golden
LinkedIn listing is active \fIand\fR a matching listing was found on the
company's own careers site. Highest-confidence leads.
.TP
.B Active
LinkedIn listing is active but no independent company careers URL was found.
.TP
.B Unknown
The LinkedIn page could not be fetched or returned an unexpected response.
.TP
.B Likely Closed
The LinkedIn listing returned 404 or contained closed-job language.
.SH FAKE-JOB DETECTION SIGNALS
The following conditions each add an entry to \fBfake_reasons\fR:
.PP
.RS
\(bu Phrases: unlimited earning/income, be your own boss, work from anywhere,
financial freedom, passive income, MLM/multi-level marketing/network marketing,
commission-only, no experience necessary/required, earn $NNN+ per day/week,
set your own hours/schedule, pyramid, Amway, Primerica, Cutco, Vector
Marketing, Herbalife, Aviator, 1099 contractor
.PP
\(bu Company name matches: independent business owner, self-employed, your own
business
.PP
\(bu Title matches: life insurance sales/agent, insurance sales agent, financial
advisor/representative, sales representative (commission), recruitment
consultant (commission)
.PP
\(bu Snippet present but shorter than 60 characters
.PP
\(bu Company name is empty, "Confidential", or "Undisclosed"
.RE
.SH EXAMPLES
Default run — LinkedIn, Salt Lake City, full verify, saves to jobs.csv:
.PP
.RS
.nf
python3 job_scraper.py
.fi
.RE
.PP
Quick scrape, no verify, different city:
.PP
.RS
.nf
python3 job_scraper.py \-\-location "Austin, TX" \-\-no-verify
.fi
.RE
.PP
Save both CSV and JSON with a longer delay:
.PP
.RS
.nf
python3 job_scraper.py \-\-delay 3.0 \-\-output jobs.csv \-\-json jobs.json
.fi
.RE
.PP
Fast test run (5 results per term, no verify):
.PP
.RS
.nf
python3 job_scraper.py \-\-max-per-term 5 \-\-no-verify
.fi
.RE
.SH NOTES
LinkedIn's public job search pages are rendered client-side; the static HTML
returned by a plain HTTP request does not include job description text. As a
result, the \fBsnippet\fR field is often empty for LinkedIn results and
snippet-based fake-job heuristics may not fire.
.PP
LinkedIn may rate-limit or block requests. Increasing \fB\-\-delay\fR reduces
this risk.
.PP
\fBverify_jobs()\fR makes two HTTP requests per active job (one LinkedIn
check, one DuckDuckGo search). On large result sets this can take several
minutes.
.SH DEPENDENCIES
.B requests, beautifulsoup4, lxml
.SH AUTHOR
B0bTheSkull
